metadata.name: Night Spell
metadata.description:
It's late
The sun goes down and gives way to the night.

I like the day, it's hot, it's busy... but at night...
The night is magic! It has an air of mystery that fascinates me.

Here the magic seems to go further, because it is when the sun goes out that they light up!
The lamps indicate the way and the waters of the high tide that invade the streets reflect all this brightness.

The silence, the brightness, the reflection, the darkness
We're paralyzed under the spell of the night
So we can only admire.


_

This photograph was taken in 2021, in the city of PARATY - RJ / BRAZIL
The city, considered a National Historic Landmark, was designed in the 17th century so that during high tide periods, sea water would enter and leave the streets as a natural way of cleaning them.
